<br>
Currently atomic plants are protected by small contingents of private security guards armed with light weapons. Some plants have also been temporarily beefed up with lightly armed small teams of National Guard Weekend Warriors.<br>
<br>
Meserve has adamantly refused to have anti-aircraft missiles or any heavy weapons used at atomic plants. (He fears that these devices could be used deliberately or accidently to destroy the reactors)<br>
<br>
From the beginning, he has insisted that the best protection is better passenger screening at airports and having the FAA tell people not to fly aircraft into nuclear plants.<br>
<br>
It isn't suprising that the NRC concluded what the boss expected going in. Congress is not going to sit still for this avoidance of responsibility.<br>
<br>
See this typical news report from way back in May:<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> May 14, 2002<br>
